Tip 1:

rfkill list all
sudo rfkill unblock wifi

Tip 2:

sudo dhcpd -4

Tip 3 :

I fixed this problemo on my freshly installed Raspbian Buster with one WIERD trick :twisted: it worked like a CHARM :mrgreen:
Code: Select all

cd ../../..
sudo mv /etc/wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant.conf.original /etc/wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant.conf
What I did next with this one extra step was not at all excruciating :twisted:
Code: Select all

 'sudo raspi-config" 

Under localisation, change WLAN country to your location

Tip 4 :

Setting my locale to en us utf8 resolved this issue.
